WEBVTT

00:01.387 --> 00:04.178
♪♪♪

00:05.220 --> 00:06.261
[Ronnie]
Previously on  The Chi...

00:06.345 --> 00:07.512
May I help you?

00:07.595 --> 00:10.428
[groaning]
Stop!

00:10.512 --> 00:11.595
Fuck beats up an old lady?

00:11.679 --> 00:13.053
It's a wonder she's alive.

00:13.136 --> 00:14.553
[Ronnie] I need
to make a call.

00:14.637 --> 00:15.720
I need to see
if my grandmother's

00:15.804 --> 00:16.679
out of surgery now.

00:16.762 --> 00:17.929
I'll see what I can do.

00:18.011 --> 00:20.011
But you need to calm
the fuck down.

00:20.095 --> 00:21.470
But I already talked to them.

00:21.553 --> 00:24.095
Ronnie Davis is trying
to get out of jail.

00:24.178 --> 00:26.595
You talking to the DA
could help put him away.

00:26.679 --> 00:28.136
That was cool,
what you did for Junie.

00:28.220 --> 00:30.303
I'll take it as gratitude,

00:30.387 --> 00:31.679
'cause our debt is settled.

00:31.762 --> 00:33.637
♪ suspenseful music ♪

00:33.720 --> 00:34.637
[camera shutter clicking]

00:34.720 --> 00:36.053
Maisha--
[groans]

00:36.136 --> 00:37.512
- You like my hair?
- It's nice.

00:38.553 --> 00:39.887
[groans]

00:39.970 --> 00:41.095
I'll give you
whatever you want.

00:41.178 --> 00:42.679
Just show me
who killed my brother.

00:42.762 --> 00:45.261
I'll take the wheels.

00:45.345 --> 00:46.303
[Maisha] What about the bike?

00:46.387 --> 00:47.512
I'm lending it to you.

00:47.595 --> 00:49.053
You know,
for the baby and stuff.

00:49.136 --> 00:51.887
[Kimberly] Are you a drunk,
Mr. Davis?

00:51.970 --> 00:53.136
Stop drinking
that fucking pruno

00:53.220 --> 00:54.595
so I can get you
out of here.

00:54.679 --> 00:56.136
Smell like shit.

00:56.220 --> 00:58.303
You okay?

00:58.387 --> 00:59.553
I'll testify.

00:59.637 --> 01:01.136
Hold up.

01:01.220 --> 01:02.470
Hold up!

01:02.553 --> 01:03.970
What's your name,
you little badass?

01:04.053 --> 01:05.845
Jason.

01:11.970 --> 01:16.011
♪ I got to get back
to my baby ♪

01:16.095 --> 01:20.595
♪ I got to get back,
I got to get back, hey ♪

01:20.679 --> 01:24.929
♪ It's been 40 days
and 40 nights ♪

01:25.011 --> 01:27.303
♪ I'm so lonesome
and blue... ♪

01:27.387 --> 01:29.970
Really, Ronnie?
Three waffles?

01:30.053 --> 01:31.887
The last thing I need
is this boy on a sugar high.

01:31.970 --> 01:33.136
He barely concentrates
on anything

01:33.220 --> 01:34.804
other than basketball
as it is.

01:34.887 --> 01:36.178
Oh, let him have it,

01:36.261 --> 01:37.595
just for today.

01:37.679 --> 01:39.220
No school,
parent-teacher conferences--

01:39.303 --> 01:40.762
Can I have some more syrup?

01:40.845 --> 01:42.595
[Tracy] See?

01:42.679 --> 01:45.053
And I made you a sandwich
to go, hmm?

01:45.136 --> 01:46.804
I know how you like to eat
in the car on the way to work.

01:46.887 --> 01:48.595
- Thank you.
- Mmm.

01:48.679 --> 01:51.553
I can't believe you did
all this before 7 a.m.

01:51.637 --> 01:53.512
I'm still on military time.

01:53.595 --> 01:54.845
I'm sorry.

01:54.929 --> 01:56.512
Don't apologize.

01:56.595 --> 01:58.303
I think it's sweet.

01:58.970 --> 02:00.595
- Mm.
- Ew!

02:00.679 --> 02:01.929
Boy, go brush your teeth.

02:03.679 --> 02:08.011
♪ The time that I spent away ♪

02:08.095 --> 02:12.804
♪ Sure has taken its toll... ♪

02:12.887 --> 02:15.178
So what do you got
planned today?

02:15.261 --> 02:17.387
Gonna go head over
to my grandma's,

02:17.470 --> 02:19.595
gonna cut her grass,
do some work around the house,

02:19.679 --> 02:22.637
and after that, me and J
are just gonna hang out,

02:22.720 --> 02:24.512
see what we
can get into.

02:26.053 --> 02:29.178
Thought you were gonna go over
to the post office.

02:29.261 --> 02:30.553
I heard on the news,
they were hiring, like,

02:30.637 --> 02:31.720
a hundred new mail carriers.

02:31.804 --> 02:33.595
I'm on it, babe.

02:33.679 --> 02:36.095
I'm gonna get
a good job real soon.

02:36.178 --> 02:39.720
It's only been a few months
since I got back.

02:39.804 --> 02:42.887
Come here.
Come on.

02:42.970 --> 02:46.011
♪ dramatic music ♪

02:46.095 --> 02:49.011
♪♪♪

02:49.095 --> 02:51.178
I'm gonna take care
of you guys.

02:51.261 --> 02:53.136
♪♪♪

02:53.220 --> 02:55.428
Come on.
You have my word on that.

02:55.512 --> 03:00.387
♪♪♪

03:01.220 --> 03:02.887
[audio fast-forwarding]

03:02.970 --> 03:05.887
We argue.

03:05.970 --> 03:08.387
I took out the gun and...

03:10.387 --> 03:12.303
[audio fast-forwarding]

03:12.387 --> 03:14.011
[Cruz] I need
to hear you say it.

03:14.095 --> 03:16.261
I shot him.

03:16.345 --> 03:17.804
That was it.

03:17.887 --> 03:20.178
[audio rewinding]

03:20.261 --> 03:22.679
[Cruz] I need
to hear you say it.

03:22.762 --> 03:24.762
I shot him.

03:24.845 --> 03:26.470
That was it.

03:29.220 --> 03:31.428
Ronald Davis'
toxicology report.

03:31.512 --> 03:32.804
Should I do the honors,
or would you like to?

03:32.887 --> 03:34.720
Go ahead.

03:34.804 --> 03:37.178
His blood alcohol level
was twice the legal limit

03:37.261 --> 03:39.011
on the night
of the confession,

03:39.095 --> 03:42.387
with trace amounts
of barbiturates and a sedative.

03:42.470 --> 03:45.011
Sarge, he shot that kid.

03:45.095 --> 03:46.720
We know that.
Now prove it.

03:46.804 --> 03:48.345
He described the gun.

03:48.428 --> 03:49.762
He took a chain off the body.

03:49.845 --> 03:52.220
He confessed on tape,
for Christ's sake.

03:52.303 --> 03:54.512
All while being drunk
off his ass.

03:57.178 --> 03:59.095
My work on this case was solid.

03:59.178 --> 04:01.178
There's an eyewitness.

04:01.261 --> 04:03.428
You better make sure this kid
is solid, because you know

04:03.512 --> 04:06.136
what it means if this
confession doesn't stick.

04:06.220 --> 04:08.512
It's the Board of Review
and IA breathing down

04:08.595 --> 04:09.929
both our necks.

04:10.011 --> 04:11.470
I signed off on this thing.

04:11.553 --> 04:12.804
I need you to fix it.

04:12.887 --> 04:15.720
♪ tense music ♪

04:15.804 --> 04:18.720
♪ dramatic hip-hop music ♪

04:18.804 --> 04:23.720
♪♪♪

04:25.303 --> 04:27.303
[fryers sizzling]

04:27.387 --> 04:29.095
So my pops got, like,
this small African village

04:29.178 --> 04:30.762
over there, right?

04:30.845 --> 04:32.136
Okay, yeah, I know I got
a lot of kids too,

04:32.220 --> 04:33.845
but I'm saying
this shit's crazy.

04:33.929 --> 04:35.261
I got no privacy.

04:35.345 --> 04:37.178
I gotta wait in line
to take a piss.

04:37.261 --> 04:38.929
And my stepmom,
she buy groceries

04:39.011 --> 04:40.387
Saturday morning.

04:40.470 --> 04:42.345
Tuesday night,
all the food be gone.

04:42.428 --> 04:43.762
No almond milk, nothing.

04:43.845 --> 04:45.679
You gotta start putting
your name on shit.

04:45.762 --> 04:47.387
No, they don't respect that.

04:47.470 --> 04:49.011
You better figure it out.

04:49.095 --> 04:50.470
Can't call yourself no man

04:50.553 --> 04:52.220
if you don't take care
of your kids.

04:52.303 --> 04:54.595
The-the system is rigged
against fathers.

04:54.679 --> 04:56.261
They're grilling me
like I'm fucking O.J.

04:56.345 --> 04:58.095
while she get
to just sit there.

04:58.178 --> 05:00.887
She doing what she's supposed
to--be a good mama.

05:00.970 --> 05:02.428
So the court can take money
out of my pocket

05:02.512 --> 05:04.637
but won't help me
see my son?

05:04.720 --> 05:05.929
That's some bullshit.

05:06.011 --> 05:07.053
[engine rumbling]

05:07.136 --> 05:09.178
Ain't this about a bitch?

05:11.011 --> 05:12.845
What the hell is he doing?

05:12.929 --> 05:14.679
Oh, I know dude.
I got this.

05:16.804 --> 05:18.553
Yo, you Brandon, right?

05:18.637 --> 05:20.178
Yeah, I'll be ready
for orders in a minute.

05:20.261 --> 05:22.220
Bro, I don't want
no damn tacos.

05:22.303 --> 05:24.428
You can't park right here.
This is a place of business.

05:24.512 --> 05:25.762
This is a business too.

05:25.845 --> 05:27.303
On wheels.

05:27.387 --> 05:29.220
Then wheel your ass
on up out of here.

05:29.303 --> 05:31.220
Man, me and Sonny sell
two different things.

05:31.303 --> 05:32.512
People want fried chicken,

05:32.595 --> 05:34.053
they gonna come
to y'all regardless.

05:34.136 --> 05:35.303
If they wanna try
something different

05:35.387 --> 05:36.220
and maybe expand
their palate a little bit,

05:36.303 --> 05:38.220
they'll come check me out.

05:38.303 --> 05:39.512
Man, why don't you take
this roach coach up the block?

05:39.595 --> 05:40.929
You need to pump
your fucking brakes.

05:41.011 --> 05:43.220
Don't be calling my shit
no roach coach.

05:43.303 --> 05:45.136
It's named after my brother,
and I'm only parking here

05:45.220 --> 05:46.845
because the rest of the block
is permit only.

05:46.929 --> 05:48.136
Then get a fucking permit.

05:48.220 --> 05:50.220
Today ain't the day, dog.

05:51.512 --> 05:53.303
Look, man.

05:53.387 --> 05:55.470
I don't know why
you going all crazy.

05:55.553 --> 05:57.470
But I'm not about
to fight you over no chicken.

06:02.470 --> 06:03.679
You know what?
Fuck it.

06:03.762 --> 06:04.804
You win.

06:04.887 --> 06:06.470
Everybody wins.

06:06.553 --> 06:07.970
Except Brandon.

06:09.720 --> 06:12.303
[engine rumbling]

06:12.387 --> 06:14.929
Yo, Emmett, there's something
wrong with Sonny.

06:15.011 --> 06:16.553
What?

06:17.804 --> 06:19.053
[Terry] He had this
weird look on his face,

06:19.136 --> 06:20.470
and then he just fell.

06:20.553 --> 06:21.595
I think he overheated
or something.

06:21.679 --> 06:23.845
Sonny, can you hear me?

06:23.929 --> 06:26.428
You get...get that boy

06:26.512 --> 06:29.845
to move his damn truck?

06:29.929 --> 06:31.970
Sonny, Sonny, try to--
try to smile for me.

06:32.053 --> 06:34.220
♪ dramatic music ♪

06:34.303 --> 06:36.220
Call 911.
I think he having a stroke.

06:36.303 --> 06:41.428
♪♪♪

06:45.845 --> 06:48.053
[Nina] There's nothing
to be nervous about, Kevin.

06:48.136 --> 06:49.470
You just tell the truth.

06:49.553 --> 06:51.053
That's right.
We'll be in there with you.

06:51.136 --> 06:52.011
You think that Ronnie guy
is gonna be in there

06:52.095 --> 06:53.804
with the judge?
I mean,

06:53.887 --> 06:54.970
he does have the right
to face his accuser,

06:55.053 --> 06:56.637
something like that.

06:56.720 --> 06:59.428
Boy, sometimes you're too smart
for your own good.

06:59.512 --> 07:00.929
You're gonna worry me to death.

07:01.011 --> 07:02.679
Saw it on Law & Order: SVU.

07:04.303 --> 07:05.428
Let's go, son.

07:10.512 --> 07:11.720
[man] Ms. Williams?

07:12.637 --> 07:13.970
Yes, are they ready for us?

07:14.053 --> 07:15.303
Uh, I spoke with
the judge's secretary.

07:15.387 --> 07:17.261
It'll be another few moments.

07:17.345 --> 07:18.720
I'm Alfred Justin with the
Advocacy Group for Children.

07:18.804 --> 07:20.679
- Hey.
- Hi.

07:20.762 --> 07:22.345
We work with kids and parents
who unfortunately find

07:22.428 --> 07:24.011
themselves involved in some way
with the court system.

07:24.095 --> 07:25.261
Are you an attorney?

07:25.345 --> 07:26.929
No, our work
is in social services.

07:27.011 --> 07:29.261
It's incredibly brave of you
to let Kevin testify.

07:29.345 --> 07:30.845
I've helped families
in the past deal with

07:30.929 --> 07:33.512
the pressures and sometimes
the unfortunate consequences

07:33.595 --> 07:35.011
of giving testimony,
particularly in cases

07:35.095 --> 07:36.512
of this magnitude.

07:36.595 --> 07:38.095
Consequences?

07:40.261 --> 07:42.470
Uh, can we have a minute?

07:43.762 --> 07:46.720
♪ dramatic music ♪

07:46.804 --> 07:51.679
♪♪♪

07:52.387 --> 07:55.512
[conversing indistinctly]

07:57.553 --> 08:02.679
♪♪♪

08:12.428 --> 08:13.595
What'd he say, Mom?

08:13.679 --> 08:14.762
Nothing you need
to worry about.

08:14.845 --> 08:15.887
Come on.
We're leaving.

08:15.970 --> 08:16.762
You've done more than enough.

08:16.845 --> 08:17.804
[Kevin] But, Mom--

08:17.887 --> 08:20.178
[Nina] I said come on, Kevin.

08:20.261 --> 08:25.345
♪♪♪

08:32.053 --> 08:34.178
Thank you for the assist.

08:34.261 --> 08:39.428
♪♪♪

08:39.512 --> 08:41.387
[man speaking indistinctly
over TV]

08:41.470 --> 08:43.095
[door opens]

08:43.178 --> 08:44.595
[door closes]

08:44.679 --> 08:46.929
[man speaking indistinctly
over TV]

08:47.011 --> 08:48.845
Hey, boy,
what's your credit score?

08:48.929 --> 08:50.929
[Brandon] Oh, shit.

08:51.011 --> 08:52.595
[Greavy] You probably somewhere
in the 600s, ain't you?

08:52.679 --> 08:54.512
Man, not right now.

08:54.595 --> 08:56.470
Nobody told you to go to that
expensive-ass culinary school.

08:56.553 --> 08:58.178
Ain't nobody told you
you gotta look through my mail

08:58.261 --> 08:59.720
or commenting on everything
under the fucking sun

08:59.804 --> 09:01.887
every time I come over here.

09:01.970 --> 09:04.720
[Greavy] DA's office
must have called you too.

09:04.804 --> 09:06.387
Yeah, they did.
I think it's fucked up.

09:06.470 --> 09:07.637
Yeah, me too.

09:07.720 --> 09:09.762
It's bullshit.
It's all bullshit.

09:09.845 --> 09:13.261
[man speaking indistinctly
over TV]

09:13.345 --> 09:16.845
Your mama said she ain't
coming back to Chicago.

09:16.929 --> 09:18.220
What? Why?

09:18.303 --> 09:20.053
She couldn't
handle being here

09:20.136 --> 09:22.011
- if Coogie's killer goes free.
- He ain't even free yet.

09:22.095 --> 09:24.679
She said her spirit told her
he was getting off.

09:24.762 --> 09:26.220
Man, she always feeling
some shit in her spirit.

09:26.303 --> 09:28.011
It ain't never positive.

09:28.095 --> 09:29.136
Why she don't feel,
"I'm gonna win the lotto,"

09:29.220 --> 09:32.011
in her spirit?

09:32.095 --> 09:33.387
[sighs]

09:33.470 --> 09:34.637
I know she drinking again too.

09:34.720 --> 09:37.595
[man speaking indistinctly
over TV]

09:40.095 --> 09:42.136
So what you gonna do,
move down there with her?

09:42.220 --> 09:44.970
I ain't leaving Chi-town, not
even for your crazy-ass mama.

09:45.053 --> 09:46.637
I was fine with moving down
to Tennessee with her,

09:46.720 --> 09:48.220
get me some barbecue,

09:48.303 --> 09:49.095
but I ain't fucking
with no Delaware.

09:49.178 --> 09:50.720
I feel that.

09:50.804 --> 09:52.762
Guess I'll catch
this overtime at CTA,

09:52.845 --> 09:55.428
then spend my off days
with my daughter and grandbaby.

09:55.512 --> 09:57.345
Keep my mind occupied.

09:57.428 --> 09:59.929
Might finish sprucing up
around here too...

10:00.011 --> 10:01.762
make it more my own.

10:01.845 --> 10:02.845
Well, don't get
too comfortable.

10:02.929 --> 10:04.512
My name's still on the deed.

10:04.595 --> 10:06.804
- Hmm.
- [intercom buzzes]

10:07.720 --> 10:09.053
The fuck he want?

10:14.637 --> 10:15.887
I guess you heard about Ronnie?

10:15.970 --> 10:17.512
I did.

10:17.595 --> 10:18.679
I can't imagine
how hard this must be

10:18.762 --> 10:19.845
for you and your family.

10:19.929 --> 10:21.720
No, you can't.

10:21.804 --> 10:24.011
I promise I am doing
everything I can

10:24.095 --> 10:26.053
to make sure
he stays behind bars.

10:27.845 --> 10:29.387
You think your mother
would be okay to write

10:29.470 --> 10:31.136
a victim impact statement?

10:31.220 --> 10:33.303
She ain't around,
so I doubt it.

10:34.428 --> 10:37.011
How could you let this happen?

10:37.095 --> 10:39.303
All these black men in jail
for shit they didn't do

10:39.387 --> 10:41.762
and this fool admits
to killing my brother on tape?

10:41.845 --> 10:43.804
How is he talking about
getting out of jail?

10:43.887 --> 10:46.804
♪ dramatic music ♪

10:46.887 --> 10:48.303
♪♪♪

10:48.387 --> 10:50.220
Your mom won't write
that statement,

10:50.303 --> 10:52.345
I think you should.

10:52.428 --> 10:53.929
♪♪♪

10:54.011 --> 10:55.512
It could really help.

10:55.595 --> 10:57.470
♪♪♪

10:57.553 --> 10:59.387
Here's a better thought.

10:59.470 --> 11:01.095
How about you do your job
and leave me and my family

11:01.178 --> 11:02.512
the fuck alone?

11:02.595 --> 11:07.679
♪♪♪

11:08.845 --> 11:10.637
I believe my client's
confession was coerced

11:10.720 --> 11:12.845
by an unscrupulous detective,

11:12.929 --> 11:15.136
that he pressured his own
confidential informant

11:15.220 --> 11:17.762
into implicating himself
in a murder charge.

11:17.845 --> 11:19.637
I guess it's the detective's
fault, too,

11:19.720 --> 11:21.303
that we have an eyewitness.

11:21.387 --> 11:23.929
An eyewitness in the form
of a 12-year-old child

11:24.011 --> 11:25.720
who was clearly traumatized,

11:25.804 --> 11:27.762
who's currently in therapy,

11:27.845 --> 11:31.929
and who, by the way,
shot my client in the stomach.

11:32.011 --> 11:34.762
- Is this true?
- Yes, sir.

11:34.845 --> 11:37.178
[Kimberly] Eyewitness testimony
is unreliable

11:37.261 --> 11:40.970
from adults
in the best of circumstances.

11:41.053 --> 11:43.929
Certainly that's the case
here with the kid.

11:44.011 --> 11:46.553
Thought the Ronnie Davis case
was pretty much open and shut.

11:46.637 --> 11:48.804
But in light
of new information,

11:48.887 --> 11:50.804
there's more to consider.

11:50.887 --> 11:52.720
I'll deliberate
and render my decision shortly.

11:54.261 --> 11:56.428
[school bell rings]

11:56.512 --> 11:58.804
Having sold eight boxes,

11:58.887 --> 12:01.804
Stacey Smith leads
our fund-raiser right now.

12:01.887 --> 12:04.387
Congratulations.

12:04.470 --> 12:06.929
Not to embarrass anyone
but to encourage you all

12:07.011 --> 12:08.762
to work harder to win
those great prizes

12:08.845 --> 12:10.720
for the top sellers,

12:10.804 --> 12:13.553
Lisa Gobbs
and Stanley Jackson

12:13.637 --> 12:15.762
hold the last spots.

12:15.845 --> 12:17.970
But there's still plenty
of time left and plenty of room

12:18.053 --> 12:19.220
for improvement.

12:19.303 --> 12:22.470
Man, Kev.
I gotta level up.

12:22.553 --> 12:24.136
Shedd Aquarium's weak.

12:24.220 --> 12:27.011
Penguins and sharks
are straight, but that's it.

12:27.095 --> 12:29.387
But I need this flat-screen.

12:29.470 --> 12:31.011
I'm redoing the Papa Cave.

12:31.095 --> 12:33.303
To win the flat-screen,
you gotta sell 30 boxes.

12:33.387 --> 12:37.303
Twelve candy bars a box,
360 bars, at two dollars a pop

12:37.387 --> 12:41.387
is 720 bucks for a TV
that retails at $400

12:41.470 --> 12:43.679
that the school gets for free
as a donation.

12:43.762 --> 12:45.011
Ain't nobody got time for that.

12:45.095 --> 12:47.011
Who are you, Rain Man?

12:47.095 --> 12:48.637
You don't understand.

12:48.720 --> 12:51.303
There's only one good TV
in the whole house.

12:51.387 --> 12:53.261
Ain't nobody got time to be
watching the Gospel Channel

12:53.345 --> 12:55.428
- all day long.
- Man, be weak if you want to.

12:55.512 --> 12:57.303
[Gasca] Great work, everybody.
Keep on selling.

12:57.387 --> 12:59.637
Mr. Williams,
may I have a word?

13:03.345 --> 13:05.553
If you're not going
to sell candy,

13:05.637 --> 13:07.261
could you at least not
call the aquarium weak

13:07.345 --> 13:08.470
in front of the whole class?

13:08.553 --> 13:09.845
But the aquarium's weak.

13:09.929 --> 13:11.762
It's not about you,
Mr. Williams.

13:11.845 --> 13:13.345
Your parents can afford
to take you to the aquarium.

13:13.428 --> 13:15.470
This fund-raiser
is about students

13:15.553 --> 13:17.387
who aren't as fortunate.

13:17.470 --> 13:18.595
My bad.

13:20.136 --> 13:23.178
So...no more bad-mouthing
the candy sale or the aquarium.

13:23.261 --> 13:24.720
Deal?

13:27.178 --> 13:32.095
And since you clearly
know the math,

13:32.178 --> 13:34.553
I expect you to return
on Friday with $24 in sales.

13:34.637 --> 13:35.929
- But--
- Think of it as doing

13:36.011 --> 13:39.011
a good deed
for your fellow classmate.

13:43.345 --> 13:44.178
[sighs]

13:45.428 --> 13:47.178
That thing you asked for.

13:48.470 --> 13:50.720
Thank you.

13:50.804 --> 13:53.637
So...

13:53.720 --> 13:54.845
how'd it go?

13:56.637 --> 13:58.470
I laid out all the points.
It's a solid case.

13:58.553 --> 14:01.136
Now it's up to the judge.

14:01.220 --> 14:03.178
And what about the eyewitness?

14:04.095 --> 14:05.637
I wouldn't worry about that.

14:09.220 --> 14:11.428
You been keeping
your nose clean?

14:11.512 --> 14:13.470
You tell me.
You're the bloodhound.

14:16.470 --> 14:18.220
You smell better
than before.

14:20.053 --> 14:21.887
Well, thank you for taking
my case pro bono.

14:23.845 --> 14:25.887
It's nice having someone
on your side.

14:28.637 --> 14:30.845
Mr. Davis...

14:30.929 --> 14:33.720
I've never been
on your side.

14:33.804 --> 14:35.011
You think I enjoy
getting murderers

14:35.095 --> 14:36.553
and white supremicists off?

14:36.637 --> 14:38.845
♪ dramatic music ♪

14:38.929 --> 14:40.470
I'm trying to make partner.

14:40.553 --> 14:43.011
♪♪♪

14:43.095 --> 14:45.178
I'll let you know
when I hear something.

14:45.261 --> 14:49.136
♪♪♪

14:49.220 --> 14:50.929
[door buzzes, clicks open]

14:52.553 --> 14:54.595
[Papa] At least you didn't
have to see him.

14:54.679 --> 14:55.887
If he gets out of jail,
think he'll come

14:55.970 --> 14:57.303
looking for you again?

14:57.387 --> 14:58.970
I don't know.

14:59.053 --> 15:00.720
I hope not,

15:00.804 --> 15:02.428
'cause all that drama with him
chasing you last time

15:02.512 --> 15:03.887
aggravated my asthma.

15:03.970 --> 15:05.428
Everything aggravates
your asthma.

15:05.512 --> 15:06.387
So you ain't scared
of him no more?

15:06.470 --> 15:07.637
Hell no.

15:07.720 --> 15:09.387
I ain't scared of that nigga.

15:09.470 --> 15:11.095
I never was.

15:12.053 --> 15:14.970
Cool, but just in case,
you want me to have the elders

15:15.053 --> 15:16.762
at the church pray
and lay hands on you?

15:16.845 --> 15:18.762
No, y'all be
slapping oil on people

15:18.845 --> 15:20.512
and getting the Holy Ghost
too much.

15:20.595 --> 15:22.470
But that stuff works.

15:22.553 --> 15:24.345
Last week, my dad knocked
me out with the Holy Ghost.

15:24.428 --> 15:27.178
I woke up the next morning
and aced my math test.

15:27.261 --> 15:29.637
Yeah, uh, I'm cool.

15:29.720 --> 15:32.261
[Papa] Kev, who can we finesse
to get these candy bars off?

15:32.345 --> 15:34.303
We?
You mean you.

15:35.428 --> 15:37.053
What the--

15:37.136 --> 15:39.804
How Maisha gonna give the bike
back that I gave her?

15:39.887 --> 15:42.428
I know she not calling herself
trying to be nice.

15:43.261 --> 15:44.470
[both] No.

15:44.553 --> 15:46.095
♪ hip-hop music ♪

15:46.178 --> 15:47.595
Hold on.
Don't touch it.

15:47.679 --> 15:49.345
Wait, what?
What?

15:49.428 --> 15:51.512
Yo, we don't know
what kinda criminal activity

15:51.595 --> 15:53.679
Maisha has been
getting into.

15:53.762 --> 15:55.553
Was she even at school today?

15:55.637 --> 15:57.011
Um, nope.

15:57.095 --> 15:58.637
Exactly.

15:58.720 --> 15:59.929
If I was you,
I'd ride that shit

16:00.011 --> 16:01.637
straight back to her ass.

16:01.720 --> 16:03.595
You can't be out here
riding dirty, Kev.

16:03.679 --> 16:06.220
♪♪♪

16:06.303 --> 16:08.345
[Cruz] Anybody witness you
shooting Coogie?

16:08.428 --> 16:10.679
Yeah.

16:10.762 --> 16:12.011
[Cruz] Name?

16:12.095 --> 16:12.887
[Ronnie] Kevin.

16:12.970 --> 16:15.261
Cruz, you got a minute?

16:15.345 --> 16:17.095
I'm, uh, kind of
in the middle of something.

16:17.178 --> 16:19.929
It's cool.
It'll only take a sec.

16:21.053 --> 16:22.387
I got no priors
on Brandon Johnson,

16:22.470 --> 16:24.720
but who's this guy?

16:24.804 --> 16:27.011
Homies showed him mad love
at the repast.

16:27.095 --> 16:28.470
That's Reginald Taylor.

16:28.553 --> 16:30.220
People call him Reg.

16:30.303 --> 16:32.470
He's a street leader
of the 63rd Street Mob.

16:32.553 --> 16:35.345
Run him, you'll see he's been
a menace his whole life.

16:35.428 --> 16:37.011
That explains
all the ring kissing.

16:37.095 --> 16:39.970
He doesn't strike me
as a boss, though.

16:40.053 --> 16:42.053
I'm assuming he answers
to somebody else.

16:42.136 --> 16:44.804
Yeah, they all
answer to somebody.

16:44.887 --> 16:46.387
Gang founder's
doing double life

16:46.470 --> 16:48.428
for a body he dropped
in '89.

16:48.512 --> 16:50.428
Shot caller before Reg
was a flashy hood named Trice.

16:50.512 --> 16:53.011
Before him, it was
an old-schooler named Q.

16:53.095 --> 16:54.970
Street says both are dead.

16:55.053 --> 16:57.303
And if Reg should meet
an untimely death,

16:57.387 --> 16:59.470
who are the next knuckleheads
in succession?

17:00.929 --> 17:02.220
[keyboard clacking]

17:03.762 --> 17:06.387
[printer whirring]

17:09.053 --> 17:10.428
Appreciate you, Detective.

17:10.512 --> 17:12.470
Don't mention it.

17:12.553 --> 17:14.679
Getting used to you
interrupting me.

17:14.762 --> 17:17.679
♪ groovy music ♪

17:17.762 --> 17:21.845
♪♪♪

17:21.929 --> 17:25.428
[Sundra] My dad talks
about you all the time.

17:25.512 --> 17:28.720
You're like
a son to him.

17:28.804 --> 17:31.679
Doctor said he wouldn't be
alive if it wasn't for you.

17:32.929 --> 17:35.387
Tch, well, my mom's a nurse.

17:35.470 --> 17:37.136
She's always talking to me
about her patients.

17:37.220 --> 17:38.595
I guess some of it stuck.

17:38.679 --> 17:40.553
But look,
Sonny ain't going nowhere.

17:40.637 --> 17:41.720
He got the whole hood to feed.

17:41.804 --> 17:44.512
Yeah.
I don't know.

17:44.595 --> 17:47.303
And I'm vegan, so I don't know
the first thing about chicken.

17:47.387 --> 17:49.136
Wait, so you're thinking
about closing this place?

17:49.220 --> 17:50.470
The family has
talked about it.

17:50.553 --> 17:51.929
You can't.
I need this job.

17:52.011 --> 17:53.095
Well, I'd hate to do it,
but I--

17:53.178 --> 17:55.136
Let me run it.

17:55.220 --> 17:57.303
I can hold down the fort
till Sonny's back on his feet.

17:57.387 --> 17:59.303
But do you have any experience
running a business?

17:59.387 --> 18:00.887
I know enough.

18:00.970 --> 18:02.512
Besides, no sense
in shutting it down

18:02.595 --> 18:04.929
when it can be open,
making money, right?

18:07.220 --> 18:09.303
[hip-hop music playing
over radio]

18:09.387 --> 18:11.303
One step forward,
two steps back.

18:11.387 --> 18:13.303
That's my life.
No breaks.

18:13.387 --> 18:15.387
It's like this thing
with Coogie's killer.

18:15.470 --> 18:17.595
First he confessed
and said he did it.

18:17.679 --> 18:19.887
Now he got a new lawyer and
he's trying to get out of jail.

18:19.970 --> 18:21.178
Hey, I wouldn't sweat it.

18:21.261 --> 18:23.053
He murdered your brother
in cold blood.

18:23.136 --> 18:25.095
There's no way he's walking
scot-free for that.

18:25.178 --> 18:27.345
Yeah, you're probably right.

18:27.428 --> 18:31.011
Good thing is,
business is steady.

18:31.095 --> 18:32.345
Give me a little
breathing room

18:32.428 --> 18:33.929
to catch up
on some of these bills.

18:34.011 --> 18:35.762
Yo, speaking of bills,
you get this joint?

18:37.178 --> 18:38.929
Five grand to the winner
and a three-page spread

18:39.011 --> 18:41.845
on Great Plate Magazine
might solve your problems.

18:41.929 --> 18:44.762
Yeah, I saw that, but I might
be out of my league.

18:44.845 --> 18:46.595
Please, you're just
as good as them.

18:47.929 --> 18:50.387
- [cell phone rings]
- Shit.

18:50.470 --> 18:51.595
- Can you get that for me?
- Yeah, I got you.

18:51.679 --> 18:52.720
[cell phone beeps]

18:52.804 --> 18:54.220
Yo.

18:54.303 --> 18:55.762
Yep.

18:55.845 --> 18:57.553
Yeah, I can do that.

18:57.637 --> 18:59.428
Just send me the address.

18:59.512 --> 19:01.220
Peace.

19:01.303 --> 19:02.595
Hey, look, after we handle
this last customer,

19:02.679 --> 19:04.637
- shut it down.
- What? Why?

19:04.720 --> 19:07.011
We got another job. I'll tell
you about it on the way.

19:10.470 --> 19:12.553
♪ Ohio Players'
"Funky Worm" playing ♪

19:12.637 --> 19:15.553
♪ There's a worm
in the ground, yes, it is ♪

19:15.637 --> 19:17.220
♪ That's right,
that's right ♪

19:17.303 --> 19:20.720
♪ It lives six feet down ♪

19:20.804 --> 19:22.637
♪ Six feet down ♪

19:22.720 --> 19:27.553
♪ He only comes around ♪

19:27.637 --> 19:29.387
♪ When he wants to get down ♪

19:29.470 --> 19:31.220
♪ But when he comes out
of his hole ♪

19:31.303 --> 19:33.595
♪ He sounds something
like this... ♪

19:33.679 --> 19:38.136
♪♪♪

19:38.220 --> 19:40.845
Um, where the fuck are we,

19:40.929 --> 19:43.178
the Players Ball?

19:43.261 --> 19:45.011
Man, ever since
I did Junie's repast,

19:45.095 --> 19:46.804
I've been getting calls
off the hook.

19:46.887 --> 19:49.470
I'm in high demand
at hood funerals now.

19:49.553 --> 19:51.679
Plus, I can make
twice as much doing this

19:51.762 --> 19:54.428
as I can selling tacos on
King Drive from 12 to three.

19:54.512 --> 19:56.845
There's gotta be an easier way
to make money than this.

19:56.929 --> 19:58.345
[scoffs]
Nah, G.

19:58.428 --> 20:00.011
This the lick.

20:00.095 --> 20:01.887
Besides, in a restaurant,
I'd never be able to get

20:01.970 --> 20:03.679
to see Monkey D
and Lady Isis.

20:03.762 --> 20:05.303
- [laughs]
- Beautiful.

20:05.387 --> 20:07.720
- You feel me?
- [both laugh]

20:07.804 --> 20:10.679
[indistinct chatter]

20:15.762 --> 20:17.470
I knew you'd come.

20:17.553 --> 20:19.261
I've been all over this place
looking for your ass.

20:19.345 --> 20:20.929
I didn't know you moved.

20:21.011 --> 20:22.512
Look, I'm just here
to give you this bike back,

20:22.595 --> 20:24.220
'cause God knows
what you been doing with it.

20:24.303 --> 20:26.053
Aw, you must care.

20:26.136 --> 20:28.178
- Care about what?
- About me.

20:28.261 --> 20:30.470
I don't care about you.
On my mamas.

20:30.553 --> 20:32.845
I just don't give people stuff
and take it back.

20:32.929 --> 20:33.929
You know what?
Forget it.

20:34.011 --> 20:36.178
Wait.

20:36.261 --> 20:38.053
My mom told me to bring
the bike back.

20:38.136 --> 20:41.053
One of my snitch-ass
cousins told.

20:41.136 --> 20:44.136
But as long as you here,
I need something.

20:44.220 --> 20:45.637
You need to start
bringing me my homework

20:45.720 --> 20:47.553
every day.

20:47.637 --> 20:48.970
Now you got a ride.

20:49.053 --> 20:51.553
No.
I'm not your slave.

20:51.637 --> 20:53.136
You would be so lucky.

20:53.220 --> 20:55.261
[chuckles]

20:55.345 --> 20:58.303
Do it, or I'll tell Mrs. Jones
about that volcano

20:58.387 --> 20:59.804
y'all stole from the library

20:59.887 --> 21:01.595
and get you
and your little friends

21:01.679 --> 21:02.887
in trouble.

21:03.011 --> 21:05.553
Damn, Maisha.
Thought we was cool.

21:05.637 --> 21:07.303
Just bring me my homework, boy.

21:09.303 --> 21:11.845
[monitor beeping]

21:11.929 --> 21:14.804
♪ dramatic music ♪

21:14.887 --> 21:17.512
♪♪♪

21:17.595 --> 21:20.220
[Jada] Miss Ethel,
this is Detective Toussaint.

21:21.512 --> 21:23.512
Miss Davis, I wanna talk to you
about what you remember

21:23.595 --> 21:25.679
about the attack.

21:25.762 --> 21:27.553
Would you recognize any
of the men if you saw them?

21:27.637 --> 21:30.845
♪♪♪

21:30.929 --> 21:32.303
[Ethel] No.

21:32.387 --> 21:34.595
I know that boy.

21:34.679 --> 21:36.804
But it-it wasn't him.

21:36.887 --> 21:40.887
♪♪♪

21:42.387 --> 21:43.762
[Jada] Yeah, take it slow.

21:45.637 --> 21:47.303
Can you describe
who attacked you?

21:47.387 --> 21:49.178
Now, that I can do.

21:51.011 --> 21:52.178
He was black.

21:52.261 --> 21:54.303
♪♪♪

21:54.387 --> 21:56.011
Smiled a lot.

21:56.095 --> 21:58.720
Tall.

21:58.804 --> 21:59.970
And ugly something.

22:00.053 --> 22:01.845
♪♪♪

22:01.929 --> 22:04.720
And said he was a homeless vet.

22:04.804 --> 22:06.845
You said, "He."

22:06.929 --> 22:07.887
There was only one attacker?

22:07.970 --> 22:09.220
[groans]

22:09.303 --> 22:10.929
- [coughing]
- [alarms beeping]

22:11.011 --> 22:12.595
[Jada] Okay.

22:12.679 --> 22:14.011
[coughing]

22:14.095 --> 22:15.720
I'm all right.
I'm all right.

22:15.804 --> 22:17.011
I'm sorry.
She needs her rest.

22:17.095 --> 22:18.762
You should come back later.

22:18.845 --> 22:21.970
[coughing]

22:22.053 --> 22:23.220
[indistinct chatter]

22:23.303 --> 22:24.595
[dial tone hums]

22:25.679 --> 22:28.553
[line trilling]

22:32.178 --> 22:33.220
[woman] You have reached

22:33.303 --> 22:38.178
(773) 555-0155.

22:38.261 --> 22:40.637
At the tone,
please leave a message.

22:40.720 --> 22:42.053
[beep]

22:44.512 --> 22:47.053
You and that girl
must be getting serious.

22:47.136 --> 22:49.011
What's her name?
Tammy?

22:49.095 --> 22:50.929
Tracy, Grandma.

22:51.011 --> 22:53.261
I knew it was a T
some kind of way.

22:53.345 --> 22:56.053
Seems very serious
if you keeping her son.

22:56.136 --> 22:59.011
When your mama was alive,
she wouldn't let nobody

22:59.095 --> 23:01.053
watch you but me.

23:01.136 --> 23:04.011
[basketball bouncing]

23:06.387 --> 23:07.428
Grandma, how you like
if I plant you

23:07.512 --> 23:09.303
some peonies out here?

23:09.387 --> 23:11.136
[Ethel] Sounds good to me.

23:11.220 --> 23:12.804
I made some sweet tea.

23:12.887 --> 23:15.387
- Y'all want some?
- I do.

23:15.470 --> 23:18.428
- All right.
- Thanks, Grandma.

23:20.220 --> 23:21.345
[chuckles]

23:22.845 --> 23:25.470
Ronnie, who's your favorite
Bulls player right now?

23:25.553 --> 23:28.512
Jordan.
Past, present, and future.

23:28.595 --> 23:30.303
[Ethel] Ronnie,
come get this tray.

23:30.387 --> 23:32.011
Keep working
on your left hand.

23:37.929 --> 23:39.720
- [Jason] Hey!
- [boy] Go get it, scrub.

23:39.804 --> 23:42.053
Watch it there now, son.
Keep the ball over there.

23:42.136 --> 23:44.887
- Whatever.
- Don't you "whatever" me.

23:44.970 --> 23:47.303
- You call me sir, understand?
- Hey, hey, hey!

23:47.387 --> 23:49.303
Don't you put your hands
on my son!

23:49.387 --> 23:52.178
♪ dramatic music ♪

23:52.261 --> 23:53.428
What'd I tell you about keeping

23:53.512 --> 23:54.929
- that ball over here, huh?
- Ow!

23:55.011 --> 23:56.553
You need to stay
on this side of the street!

23:56.637 --> 23:58.387
You're hurting me!

23:58.470 --> 24:00.929
- You ain't my daddy!
- Hmm.

24:01.011 --> 24:02.929
I'm ready to go home.

24:03.011 --> 24:05.762
Jason, come back here!

24:05.845 --> 24:07.970
♪♪♪

24:08.053 --> 24:12.053
[indistinct chatter]

24:12.136 --> 24:14.011
Damn, burner's out.

24:14.095 --> 24:15.887
Oh, we served that much food?

24:15.970 --> 24:17.553
[Brandon] You mean they ate
that much food.

24:17.637 --> 24:19.762
That was a gang of people.
I'm tired as hell.

24:19.845 --> 24:21.512
Now I gotta use what I was
gonna make off this job

24:21.595 --> 24:23.345
to fix this shit.

24:23.428 --> 24:25.387
Didn't I just say?
Two steps back.

24:25.470 --> 24:28.345
Hey, B, let me holler at you
right fast, young blood.

24:28.428 --> 24:31.303
♪ soul music ♪

24:31.387 --> 24:34.637
♪♪♪

24:34.720 --> 24:36.303
♪ Well, well ♪

24:36.387 --> 24:38.345
♪ I'm amazed ♪

24:38.428 --> 24:40.303
♪ By your sensuous love... ♪

24:40.387 --> 24:45.553
♪♪♪

24:45.637 --> 24:47.470
Man, I sure do appreciate you
coming through for me like that

24:47.553 --> 24:49.261
on such short notice.

24:49.345 --> 24:50.804
Cousin Mildred was supposed
to did all the food.

24:50.887 --> 24:52.053
She messed around,
got called in for a double.

24:52.136 --> 24:53.053
You understand, playboy.

24:53.136 --> 24:54.720
It's all good, Smitty.

24:54.804 --> 24:56.762
- You ready to get settled up?
- Yes, sir.

24:56.845 --> 24:58.303
Let's handle this biz and I'll
get back to these streets.

24:58.387 --> 25:00.470
It's gonna be 1,500 even.

25:00.553 --> 25:03.303
Fifteen hundred?

25:03.387 --> 25:05.303
You said 850.

25:05.387 --> 25:07.011
I mean, that's
when you told me

25:07.095 --> 25:08.553
it was gonna be 60 people
I was cooking for.

25:08.637 --> 25:10.553
Half of Lawndale
showed up out here.

25:10.637 --> 25:12.762
Oh, boy, you got that
Ronald Reagan inflation

25:12.845 --> 25:14.095
around this piece.

25:14.178 --> 25:16.053
[laughs]
I got you, though.

25:16.136 --> 25:19.595
♪♪♪

25:19.679 --> 25:20.261
What am I supposed
to do with this?

25:20.345 --> 25:21.470
[chuckles]

25:21.553 --> 25:23.053
That's that
Ooh-Wee Teena Marie.

25:23.136 --> 25:25.345
You bag that up right,
you got 700 right fast.

25:25.428 --> 25:26.387
By the time it's all
said and done,

25:26.470 --> 25:27.970
you might mess around,
owe me, blood.

25:28.053 --> 25:29.220
[chuckles]

25:29.303 --> 25:34.470
♪♪♪

25:43.095 --> 25:44.887
I wanna speak
to your supervisor.

25:44.970 --> 25:46.345
What seems to be the problem?

25:46.428 --> 25:48.261
The problem is
her funky attitude.

25:48.345 --> 25:50.136
And you're out of dark meat.

25:50.220 --> 25:51.637
Oh, I apologize for that,
ma'am.

25:51.720 --> 25:53.345
Um, we cooking up
another batch right now.

25:53.428 --> 25:55.595
She said that
30 minutes ago.

25:55.679 --> 25:58.512
Can you please be nice
to the customers?

25:58.595 --> 26:00.470
[hip-hop music playing
over speakers]

26:00.553 --> 26:01.261
And where the hell is Rhonda?

26:01.345 --> 26:02.470
She called off.

26:02.553 --> 26:03.387
Said she ain't feel
like dealing

26:03.470 --> 26:04.887
with these people today.

26:04.970 --> 26:06.470
[Emmett] Neither do I,
but I still showed up.

26:06.553 --> 26:08.220
- Folks is trifling.
- Mm.

26:08.303 --> 26:09.428
Terry, how much longer
on the chicken?

26:09.512 --> 26:11.220
I'm moving as fast as I can,
bro.

26:11.303 --> 26:13.845
I only got one fryer.
[scoffs]

26:13.929 --> 26:16.053
And that grease trap is still
backed up on the other one.

26:16.136 --> 26:18.095
Who was supposed to clean
the grease trap?

26:18.887 --> 26:20.679
You.

26:20.762 --> 26:22.845
Fuck.

26:22.929 --> 26:24.387
Sundra need to close
this place,

26:24.470 --> 26:25.762
'cause you don't know
what you doing.

26:25.845 --> 26:28.428
What you say?
What you say?

26:28.512 --> 26:29.762
Man, get back to work.

26:29.845 --> 26:31.303
Oh, so you're the manager now?

26:31.387 --> 26:33.470
Yeah, which means
I can fire people.

26:33.553 --> 26:35.804
[man] Sir, this chicken
is burnt.

26:35.887 --> 26:38.762
♪♪♪

26:38.845 --> 26:39.845
Oh, it's not burnt.

26:39.929 --> 26:41.929
It's-it's-it's extra crispy.

26:42.011 --> 26:43.845
♪ Magna Carda's "The Root"
playing ♪

26:43.929 --> 26:45.470
I want my money back.

26:45.553 --> 26:50.720
♪♪♪

26:52.720 --> 26:55.136
♪ Everybody come from
somewhere or maybe nowhere ♪

26:55.220 --> 26:57.095
♪ The place you wake from ♪

26:57.178 --> 26:58.637
♪ The place we ain't from
that makes us scared ♪

26:58.720 --> 27:00.345
♪ The projects,
the overseas... ♪

27:00.428 --> 27:02.637
[man] Get off my porch!

27:02.720 --> 27:04.679
♪ Place where ain't no art
on the walls ♪

27:04.762 --> 27:06.679
♪ Just pictures of Jesus
and civil rights leaders ♪

27:06.762 --> 27:09.428
- ♪ Or confederate flags... ♪
- Go away!

27:09.512 --> 27:11.011
♪ From the plastic
of her seat ♪

27:11.095 --> 27:12.178
♪ And then
struggling mothers ♪

27:12.261 --> 27:13.011
♪ Young brothers... ♪

27:13.095 --> 27:13.845
Afternoon.

27:13.929 --> 27:15.845
Yo, go!

27:15.929 --> 27:17.887
What they running for?
Excuse me, miss.

27:17.970 --> 27:21.053
I just wanted to ask--
I have a--

27:21.136 --> 27:22.762
Come on.

27:22.845 --> 27:24.595
♪ Instead we see
who we are not ♪

27:24.679 --> 27:26.095
♪ And think they all
beneath us ♪

27:26.178 --> 27:27.720
♪ 'Cause he carrying heat ♪

27:27.804 --> 27:29.720
♪ And she got
her college degree on ♪

27:29.804 --> 27:31.053
♪ 'Cause the sweetest love
done knocked you up ♪

27:31.136 --> 27:32.720
♪ And he don't
wanna keep her ♪

27:32.804 --> 27:34.470
♪ We all living different
for a reason ♪

27:34.553 --> 27:36.553
♪ We come from the root ♪

27:36.637 --> 27:39.387
[dog barking]

27:39.470 --> 27:41.762
[Gladys] Wait a minute.
This is about Ethel?

27:41.845 --> 27:43.053
I'll talk to you.

27:43.136 --> 27:44.303
[dog barking]

27:44.387 --> 27:46.053
Sit your ass down, Kang!

27:46.136 --> 27:48.178
Making all that noise.

27:48.261 --> 27:50.261
I got a noisy one too.

27:50.345 --> 27:51.679
Detective Toussaint.

27:51.762 --> 27:52.845
What's your name?

27:52.929 --> 27:55.095
Gladys, baby.
[chuckles]

27:55.178 --> 27:57.762
I've lived over here 46 years,
and I ain't scared

27:57.845 --> 27:59.178
of these Negroes.

27:59.261 --> 28:01.053
What you need to know?

28:01.887 --> 28:03.804
Recognize anybody here
as a troublemaker?

28:08.470 --> 28:10.637
I don't.

28:10.720 --> 28:13.470
You know, they all start
to look the same after a while.

28:16.136 --> 28:17.345
[Toussaint] What's with all
the "For Sale" signs?

28:17.428 --> 28:18.553
Folks want to move,

28:18.637 --> 28:20.804
it's getting so bad
around here.

28:20.887 --> 28:23.553
All the shootings,
break-ins,

28:23.637 --> 28:25.970
what they did to Ethel.

28:26.053 --> 28:27.345
It's terrible.

28:29.095 --> 28:30.804
♪ dramatic music ♪

28:30.887 --> 28:33.011
Miss Gladys,
aside from the crime,

28:33.095 --> 28:34.679
would you happen to know
if some of your neighbors

28:34.762 --> 28:36.011
have been forced
to leave their homes?

28:36.095 --> 28:38.553
Anybody been evicted recently?

28:38.637 --> 28:41.845
I don't know nothing about
nobody getting evicted.

28:41.970 --> 28:43.887
There's this white girl walking
around offering folks money

28:43.970 --> 28:46.720
to move,
so some people taking it.

28:46.804 --> 28:48.428
This white girl have a name?

28:49.303 --> 28:50.679
I don't know.

28:50.762 --> 28:51.762
If you see
that white girl again,

28:51.845 --> 28:53.220
will you please
give me a call?

28:53.303 --> 28:54.595
Sure will.

28:54.679 --> 28:55.845
- [alarm beeping]
- ♪ Wake up ♪

28:55.929 --> 28:57.595
♪ Get up, get up, go ♪

28:57.679 --> 28:59.011
♪ Get up, get up,
get up, go ♪

28:59.095 --> 29:01.220
- Huh.
- ♪ Get up, get up, go ♪

29:01.303 --> 29:02.178
♪ Get up, get up, get up,
gotta wake your ass up ♪

29:02.261 --> 29:04.136
Huh.

29:04.220 --> 29:05.428
♪ Wake up, wake up, wake up,
hey, hey ♪

29:05.512 --> 29:07.595
Huh.

29:07.679 --> 29:10.762
♪ Yeah, wake up,
right, wake up, wake up... ♪

29:10.845 --> 29:13.220
Huh.

29:13.303 --> 29:14.553
Mm.

29:14.637 --> 29:16.261
♪ Get up, get up, go ♪

29:16.345 --> 29:17.387
♪ Get up, get up,
get up, go ♪

29:17.470 --> 29:18.553
It's actually premium shit.

29:18.637 --> 29:19.595
Yes.

29:19.679 --> 29:21.553
Yeah. I could flip it.

29:21.637 --> 29:22.845
Probably get about 800 for it.

29:22.929 --> 29:24.053
That should square us
on the truck.

29:24.136 --> 29:25.929
Cool?

29:26.011 --> 29:28.720
Damn, yeah.

29:28.804 --> 29:31.011
I was gonna knock out
a couple of these other bills

29:31.095 --> 29:32.845
before I hit you back
for the truck.

29:32.929 --> 29:34.595
♪ Left the bunk
for the function... ♪

29:34.679 --> 29:36.970
[groans]

29:37.845 --> 29:39.804
How the hell you not
gonna pay me first?

29:42.428 --> 29:44.261
I'm your chief investor.

29:44.345 --> 29:46.595
Man, 'cause these bills
taking turns whupping my ass.

29:46.679 --> 29:48.637
Let me just hold 400 of this

29:48.720 --> 29:50.053
until I can get the burner
fixed and get out of this hole

29:50.136 --> 29:52.970
and then I'll pay you back
as soon as I can.

29:54.929 --> 29:56.637
I got you.
[laughs]

29:56.720 --> 29:59.470
What the hell you doing
catering pimp funerals?

29:59.553 --> 30:02.345
I'll cater anybody's funeral,
long as the check clears.

30:02.428 --> 30:05.470
No, what you need is a venture
capitalist with deep pockets.

30:05.553 --> 30:10.470
♪♪♪

30:10.553 --> 30:12.929
I got this joint in the mail
the other day.

30:13.011 --> 30:15.053
Might not help me
right this second, but...

30:15.970 --> 30:18.512
"The After Taste.
Next generation."

30:18.595 --> 30:19.804
Yeah,
it's a food competition.

30:19.887 --> 30:21.637
It's a spin
off the Taste of Chicago.

30:21.720 --> 30:23.887
In order to get in,
you gotta own a restaurant

30:23.970 --> 30:26.053
or a food truck,
be affiliated with

30:26.136 --> 30:29.303
a culinary school, and have,
like, three signature dishes.

30:29.387 --> 30:32.053
But you got all that.
Why you saying you don't know?

30:32.136 --> 30:33.470
See, this is what
I'm talking about.

30:33.553 --> 30:36.053
Your chakras,
they all out of balance.

30:36.136 --> 30:39.720
Two, three, four, five, six.
All seven of them.

30:39.804 --> 30:41.512
You'd kill this contest, bro.

30:41.595 --> 30:43.470
My school's one of the
sponsors, and you gotta be

30:43.553 --> 30:45.345
in good financial standing
to compete.

30:45.428 --> 30:47.970
Which I know you ain't.

30:51.679 --> 30:54.553
Man, it don't
even matter.

30:54.637 --> 30:58.303
Hold up, did they actually
tell you you couldn't compete?

30:59.136 --> 31:01.136
No.

31:01.220 --> 31:03.387
But you know how white people
is about they money.

31:03.470 --> 31:05.345
Boy, you better act like you
got a mouthpiece on you.

31:05.428 --> 31:06.845
You a Johnson.

31:06.929 --> 31:08.720
We make shit happen.

31:08.804 --> 31:10.095
Now, go down there
and talk somebody ear off

31:10.178 --> 31:11.679
until they let you in.

31:16.929 --> 31:18.720
- Well...
- Boy, what you doing?

31:20.762 --> 31:21.720
Mine.

31:27.387 --> 31:29.053
Here.

31:29.136 --> 31:30.553
You're getting a quiz
on linear equations.

31:30.637 --> 31:31.553
My notes are in there.

31:31.637 --> 31:32.887
Use them if you want.

31:32.970 --> 31:34.887
Have one.
They're yellow cake.

31:34.970 --> 31:36.011
I made too many.

31:38.887 --> 31:40.428
Mama got you
babysitting again?

31:41.887 --> 31:44.220
Yeah, she got another job.

31:44.303 --> 31:45.553
Your mom's got a lot of jobs.

31:45.637 --> 31:47.679
She got a lot of kids.

31:49.720 --> 31:51.220
Uh, you wanna come in?

31:51.303 --> 31:52.970
I'll wrap the rest up
for you to take

31:53.053 --> 31:54.637
to your big-boned friend Papa.

31:54.720 --> 31:56.428
I know he'll eat them.

32:00.887 --> 32:02.887
Next time, you gotta use
two hands, Sierra.

32:02.970 --> 32:04.303
Okay?

32:04.387 --> 32:05.845
No more snacks after this.

32:05.929 --> 32:07.804
It's time for y'all butts
to take a nap anyway.

32:07.887 --> 32:10.095
[child groaning]

32:12.136 --> 32:14.220
So what's the tea at school?

32:14.303 --> 32:16.970
Is Dijonay and Alexa
still beefing?

32:17.053 --> 32:19.011
No, y'all girls be
spilling tea too much.

32:19.095 --> 32:21.053
I just mind my business.

32:21.595 --> 32:23.261
You're boring.

32:24.095 --> 32:26.178
So, uh, when you coming
back to school?

32:26.261 --> 32:27.762
I don't know.

32:27.845 --> 32:28.929
My mom says she got
a lot on her plate

32:29.011 --> 32:30.512
and she needs me
right now.

32:30.595 --> 32:34.053
[baby crying]

32:34.136 --> 32:36.553
Uh, tell Papa not to eat
these all at once

32:36.637 --> 32:37.762
with his greedy self.

32:37.845 --> 32:39.011
Okay.

32:39.095 --> 32:41.261
I'll tell him.

32:41.345 --> 32:42.679
[baby crying]

32:42.762 --> 32:44.387
Uh, will I see you tomorrow?

32:46.011 --> 32:47.178
Yeah.

32:47.261 --> 32:50.053
[baby crying]

32:52.679 --> 32:54.595
Hey.
Come here.

32:54.679 --> 32:56.637
Can I have a high five?

32:56.720 --> 32:58.637
High five?

32:58.720 --> 32:59.553
Can I have a hug?

32:59.637 --> 33:01.178
[crying]

33:06.387 --> 33:09.303
♪ Melo Makes Music's
"Sleepless" playing ♪

33:09.387 --> 33:14.261
♪♪♪

33:16.345 --> 33:17.679
Coogie?

33:17.762 --> 33:19.428
♪♪♪

33:19.512 --> 33:20.804
Hey, yo, Brandon!

33:20.887 --> 33:22.679
Brandon!
Hey, yo, Brandon!

33:22.762 --> 33:24.220
♪♪♪

33:24.303 --> 33:26.428
♪ I slipped and fell ♪

33:26.512 --> 33:28.637
♪♪♪

33:28.720 --> 33:29.679
♪ On the blackest ice ♪

33:29.762 --> 33:30.804
Brandon!

33:30.887 --> 33:32.804
♪♪♪

33:32.887 --> 33:35.845
♪ Was moving at the speed
of light ♪

33:35.929 --> 33:36.887
[Kevin] Yo, Brandon!

33:36.970 --> 33:38.512
♪♪♪

33:38.595 --> 33:41.178
♪ And still overseen ♪

33:41.261 --> 33:42.136
♪ Overlooked ♪

33:42.220 --> 33:44.303
Brandon, wait up!

33:44.387 --> 33:46.345
♪ Fooled me once,
can't fool me twice, though ♪

33:46.428 --> 33:48.470
♪ I was, like, eight trying
to dance like Michael ♪

33:48.553 --> 33:50.136
♪ Cirque du Soleil,
now walk the tightrope... ♪

33:50.220 --> 33:51.512
What up, Kev?
Long time, no see.

33:51.595 --> 33:52.679
Yeah.

33:52.762 --> 33:54.887
I didn't think you saw me.

33:54.970 --> 33:56.970
You heard about that Ronnie
dude trying to get out?

33:58.970 --> 34:00.637
Yeah, I heard.

34:03.428 --> 34:05.136
Look, man, it's getting late.

34:05.220 --> 34:06.512
Put your bike in the back.
I'll give you a ride.

34:06.595 --> 34:08.428
All right. Thanks.

34:08.512 --> 34:11.387
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

34:14.595 --> 34:16.887
I just wish I could do more.

34:16.970 --> 34:18.970
I'm sorry.

34:19.053 --> 34:20.512
Don't be.

34:21.595 --> 34:23.345
Just you being willing
to speak up in the first place

34:23.428 --> 34:25.303
was helpful.

34:25.387 --> 34:27.261
Real talk.

34:27.345 --> 34:28.553
Hmm?

34:30.970 --> 34:33.929
[indistinct yelling]

34:34.011 --> 34:35.929
What you was doing all the way
on the other side of town?

34:36.011 --> 34:38.261
Dropping off some homework
to this girl at my school.

34:39.595 --> 34:41.553
[laughs]

34:41.637 --> 34:43.929
Don't let me find out you got
a little girlfriend, Kev.

34:44.011 --> 34:46.220
First of all, she ain't little.

34:46.303 --> 34:48.929
Second of all,
it ain't even like that, bro.

34:49.011 --> 34:51.303
Yeah, whatever.

34:51.387 --> 34:52.804
[scoffs]
Whatever, man.

34:52.887 --> 34:56.011
[laughs]

34:58.095 --> 34:58.970
♪ This for the dreamers ♪

34:59.053 --> 35:00.261
Let's get in on this football.

35:00.345 --> 35:02.845
♪ This for the ceaseless ♪

35:02.929 --> 35:06.804
♪ This for the scene kids,
oh, planting our seeds ♪

35:06.887 --> 35:10.053
♪ This for the sleepless ♪

35:10.136 --> 35:14.679
♪ This for my city,
I speak for the speechless ♪

35:14.762 --> 35:19.387
♪ This for my city,
departed friend ♪

35:19.470 --> 35:22.720
♪ This for my city,
my actions so sleepless ♪

35:22.804 --> 35:25.595
[grunting]

35:25.679 --> 35:27.512
You know anything about
a white lady canvassing

35:27.595 --> 35:30.804
Miss Ethel's neighborhood,
making property inquiries?

35:30.887 --> 35:32.345
No, first I've heard of that.

35:32.428 --> 35:33.595
[grunts]

35:33.679 --> 35:35.220
The Davis confession.

35:37.053 --> 35:39.136
Figured out your next move?

35:39.220 --> 35:40.845
[breathing heavily]

35:40.929 --> 35:42.178
No, there is no next move.

35:44.136 --> 35:46.720
Ronnie Davis is exactly
where he belongs.

35:46.804 --> 35:48.512
He shot that kid

35:48.595 --> 35:50.428
and confessed.

35:50.512 --> 35:52.887
Drunk, sober,
it doesn't matter.

35:52.970 --> 35:54.261
I know him.

35:54.345 --> 35:56.595
Guy's a functioning
alcoholic.

35:56.679 --> 35:58.804
Worked as my CI
for the past two years.

35:58.887 --> 36:01.428
So you took the confession
of a drunk informant?

36:01.512 --> 36:03.053
Why didn't you just tank him
till he sobered up?

36:03.136 --> 36:04.428
You know the protocol.

36:04.512 --> 36:07.804
He killed Coogie Johnson.

36:07.887 --> 36:09.762
He and I both know it.

36:09.845 --> 36:12.220
[grunting]

36:12.303 --> 36:14.053
It's all bullshit.

36:14.136 --> 36:15.887
Lawyers doing what they do:
bastardizing the law.

36:15.970 --> 36:17.553
They find loopholes,

36:17.637 --> 36:19.261
and it's our job to make sure
there aren't any.

36:19.345 --> 36:20.804
There must have been
something about this

36:20.887 --> 36:23.303
Ronnie Davis guy--
this Coogie Johnson case--

36:23.387 --> 36:25.178
that caused
the rush.

36:25.261 --> 36:26.679
[velcro ripping]

36:27.845 --> 36:29.637
I don't need a shrink.

36:29.720 --> 36:30.887
Okay?

36:32.679 --> 36:34.387
I did everything by the book.

36:36.637 --> 36:39.011
♪ Melo Makes Music's
"Sleepless" playing ♪

36:39.095 --> 36:40.595
[Kevin] That was his, right?

36:40.679 --> 36:41.553
Yeah.

36:41.637 --> 36:45.220
♪♪♪

36:45.303 --> 36:47.679
How was it like,
having a brother?

36:47.762 --> 36:49.428
Fun.
Crazy.

36:49.512 --> 36:52.136
When he was little,
he used to hate all that hair.

36:52.220 --> 36:54.762
Kids made fun of him,
called him a girl.

36:54.845 --> 36:56.720
He got into a gang of fights
over it too.

36:56.804 --> 36:58.136
Until I told him, like,
being different

36:58.220 --> 37:00.136
is what makes you special.

37:00.220 --> 37:03.136
Anyway, why?
No brothers?

37:03.220 --> 37:06.679
No, just a bossy-ass
big sister.

37:06.762 --> 37:08.804
[laughs]

37:08.887 --> 37:10.679
I'm sure she just looking out
for you, G.

37:10.762 --> 37:15.887
♪♪♪

37:16.887 --> 37:19.220
Thanks for the ride.
Dope truck.

37:19.303 --> 37:20.887
You're welcome
to roll anytime.

37:20.970 --> 37:23.387
I could always use
an extra hand.

37:23.470 --> 37:26.261
Hey, you're pretty smart
at school, right?

37:26.345 --> 37:29.845
Hmm, I'm all right,
I guess.

37:29.929 --> 37:32.428
I wanna read something to you.
Check it out.

37:32.512 --> 37:33.970
See what you think.

37:34.053 --> 37:36.220
Sure.

37:36.303 --> 37:38.053
The detective
handling Coogie's case,

37:38.136 --> 37:39.679
he asked me
to write a statement.

37:39.762 --> 37:41.303
Supposed to sway
the judge's decision

37:41.387 --> 37:43.428
about keeping
Coogie's killer in jail.

37:49.762 --> 37:51.679
Hey, look,
I'm not much of a writer,

37:51.762 --> 37:52.720
so don't be judging
my shit hard.

37:52.804 --> 37:54.637
Just read it.

37:59.553 --> 38:01.929
"My little brother, Coogie,

38:02.011 --> 38:04.428
everybody loved him.

38:04.512 --> 38:06.887
He was the glue that held
my family together.

38:06.970 --> 38:10.762
And now that he's gone,

38:10.845 --> 38:14.261
it just seems like
everything's falling apart.

38:14.345 --> 38:18.011
For me,
sometimes my mom.

38:18.095 --> 38:19.303
Even though
he was my little brother,

38:19.387 --> 38:23.303
he felt like a son to me.

38:23.387 --> 38:26.303
Because I raised him.

38:26.387 --> 38:28.762
Taught him
how to tie his shoes,

38:28.845 --> 38:31.970
how to read,
how to ride a bike.

38:32.053 --> 38:34.428
He was the light
at the end of the tunnel.

38:34.512 --> 38:36.720
♪♪♪

38:36.804 --> 38:39.387
Now there's no light.

38:39.470 --> 38:42.595
Just darkness.

38:42.679 --> 38:44.470
That's what this killer took
away from me and my family."

38:44.553 --> 38:48.679
♪♪♪

38:49.929 --> 38:52.720
That was--that was really good.

38:52.804 --> 38:55.679
Brother seemed like
a really cool guy.

38:55.762 --> 38:57.720
♪♪♪

38:57.804 --> 38:59.345
Yeah, thanks for listening,
dude.

38:59.428 --> 39:04.345
♪♪♪

39:05.845 --> 39:07.970
[sighs]

39:08.053 --> 39:10.345
♪ Fooled me once,
can't fool me twice, though ♪

39:10.428 --> 39:12.804
♪ I was, like, eight trying
to dance like Michael ♪

39:12.887 --> 39:14.970
♪ Cirque du Soleil,
now I walk the tightrope ♪

39:15.053 --> 39:15.845
♪ Learned to live ♪

39:15.929 --> 39:19.845
♪♪♪

39:19.929 --> 39:22.428
♪ This for my city and this
for the speechless... ♪

39:22.512 --> 39:24.762
[grunts]

39:24.845 --> 39:26.637
Still got my number, right?

39:26.720 --> 39:27.762
All right, well, let me know
if you need anything.

39:27.845 --> 39:29.679
- Thanks.
- All right.

39:29.762 --> 39:33.679
♪ This for my city and this
for the scene kids ♪

39:33.762 --> 39:37.929
♪ This for my city, my city,
and this for the sleepless ♪

39:38.011 --> 39:40.887
[door squeaking]

39:40.970 --> 39:42.387
[echoing thud]

39:45.011 --> 39:46.595
[radio static]

39:46.679 --> 39:49.011
Maximum range of
an M-16 A1 assault rifle's

39:49.095 --> 39:50.970
3,600 meters.

39:51.053 --> 39:54.512
Effective flying range
of 550 meters.

39:54.595 --> 39:57.387
Fires in rapid succession
800 rounds per minute.

39:57.470 --> 40:00.178
It'd be so easy
to take you out.

40:02.011 --> 40:05.053
[radio crackling]

40:05.136 --> 40:07.679
[distant gun firing]

40:07.762 --> 40:10.387
[Ethel] You been back and forth
at that window all day.

40:10.470 --> 40:12.261
What you looking for?

40:12.345 --> 40:14.470
You need to come away from it.

40:14.553 --> 40:17.136
Your disability's here.

40:17.220 --> 40:19.303
I'm not disabled.
I'm fine.

40:19.387 --> 40:21.053
Ronnie,
I need you to go downtown

40:21.136 --> 40:23.637
and pay that water bill.

40:23.720 --> 40:28.387
And get yourself together like
you been telling that girl.

40:28.470 --> 40:33.428
♪ dramatic music ♪

40:33.512 --> 40:35.136
[echoing gunfire]

40:35.220 --> 40:36.929
[Kimberly]
The DA pulled the case.

40:39.804 --> 40:41.136
What does that mean?

40:42.345 --> 40:43.512
They didn't think
they had enough evidence

40:43.595 --> 40:44.804
to move forward.

40:46.553 --> 40:47.720
You're a free man.

40:49.053 --> 40:50.470
[door buzzes]

40:51.136 --> 40:53.011
[door slams]

40:53.095 --> 40:54.303
[inhales, sighs]

40:57.261 --> 40:58.970
I don't know exactly
what to say.

40:59.053 --> 41:00.470
Say you'll do better.

41:03.303 --> 41:05.345
[distant chatter]

41:05.428 --> 41:07.929
This check is the balance
on your commissary account.

41:08.011 --> 41:09.637
I can coordinate
a halfway house

41:09.720 --> 41:11.428
if you need someplace to stay.

41:11.512 --> 41:13.595
No, I-I'm staying
with my grandma.

41:13.679 --> 41:15.804
I gotta get back
and take care of her.

41:15.887 --> 41:18.720
While your concern for your
grandmother is understandable,

41:18.804 --> 41:20.303
you won't be much use to her

41:20.387 --> 41:21.595
if you don't get
your life together.

41:21.679 --> 41:23.345
I know.

41:23.428 --> 41:24.512
It's all
I've been thinking about

41:24.595 --> 41:25.720
since she's been
in the hospital.

41:25.804 --> 41:27.220
If I was a better man,

41:27.303 --> 41:28.512
maybe this wouldn't
have happened.

41:31.011 --> 41:33.095
This probably sounds crazy,
but it's like...

41:36.053 --> 41:37.679
I been doing better in here.

41:39.428 --> 41:41.345
The order, routine.

41:43.220 --> 41:44.428
It's almost like the Army.

41:45.512 --> 41:47.845
- Almost.
- I've heard that before.

41:49.470 --> 41:51.845
Some people thrive in the
four walls of an institution

41:51.929 --> 41:56.345
but a prison can't be
the only place a man survives.

41:56.428 --> 41:58.970
You have to find structure
on the outside.

41:59.053 --> 42:01.303
You being released
is a miracle.

42:01.387 --> 42:03.637
No one walks
on a murder charge.

42:05.470 --> 42:07.553
Unless I'm defending them.

42:07.637 --> 42:10.470
♪ dramatic music ♪

42:10.553 --> 42:12.720
You have a lot to figure out,
Mr. Davis.

42:14.220 --> 42:15.637
Good luck to you.

42:15.720 --> 42:20.345
♪♪♪

42:24.303 --> 42:26.303
Is there any brisket today?

42:26.387 --> 42:28.011
No, just chicken.

42:28.095 --> 42:29.637
Uh, hush puppies?

42:29.720 --> 42:31.887
Nope, just chicken.

42:31.970 --> 42:33.762
All right, what about them
Cajun fries y'all got?

42:33.845 --> 42:36.637
Bruh, just chicken.

42:36.720 --> 42:38.095
So when y'all said,
"Sonny's Chicken Pit,"

42:38.178 --> 42:39.804
y'all really meant that shit?

42:39.887 --> 42:41.637
Look, man, this is the menu
until Sonny gets back.

42:41.720 --> 42:43.387
This all we got.

42:43.470 --> 42:46.387
[woman] I mean,
can we move it along?

42:47.512 --> 42:49.261
You want a hush puppy,
you can--

42:49.345 --> 42:52.178
[indistinct chatter]

42:54.512 --> 42:56.470
I can't believe Sonny
left you in charge.

42:56.553 --> 42:58.970
Well, believe it.
How can I help you?

42:59.053 --> 43:01.136
Look, I need some money
for EJ dentist appointment.

43:01.220 --> 43:02.595
I already gave you
your monthly check.

43:02.679 --> 43:04.345
And that barely
covers daycare.

43:04.428 --> 43:05.303
You wanted a child
support order,

43:05.387 --> 43:06.595
you got one, all right?

43:06.679 --> 43:08.428
I'm paying
what they told me to pay.

43:08.512 --> 43:09.804
Why you need to go to an
expensive-ass dentist, anyway?

43:09.887 --> 43:11.679
He only got three teeth.

43:11.762 --> 43:14.136
So you can spend $300
on a pair of gym shoes

43:14.220 --> 43:16.387
but you can't cough up
no extra money for your son?

43:16.470 --> 43:18.220
I ain't bought no new shoes
in, like, three weeks.

43:18.303 --> 43:20.136
Am I supposed to feel
sorry for you?

43:20.220 --> 43:23.095
Look, you can either order food
or get the fuck out.

43:23.178 --> 43:24.470
Fuck you, Emmett.

43:24.553 --> 43:26.720
[silverware clattering]

43:26.804 --> 43:27.762
[door opens]

43:27.845 --> 43:29.011
Sh...

43:29.095 --> 43:30.929
[door closes]

43:31.011 --> 43:33.887
[handcuffs jingling]

43:37.345 --> 43:38.845
Where you taking me?

43:38.929 --> 43:41.804
It's a briefing for inmates
within 30 days of release.

43:43.553 --> 43:45.095
Congratulations, by the way.

43:45.178 --> 43:47.178
[grunts]

43:47.261 --> 43:50.887
[both grunting]

43:50.970 --> 43:53.679
Playing your drunk card
is bullshit.

43:53.762 --> 43:56.011
[Cruz] You know it.

43:56.095 --> 43:57.095
You're the one that told me
that kid was standing

43:57.178 --> 43:58.679
over Jason's body.

43:58.762 --> 44:00.804
The fuck you think
was gonna happen?

44:00.887 --> 44:02.720
[grunts]
I looked out for you.

44:02.804 --> 44:04.053
[both breathing heavily]

44:04.136 --> 44:05.762
Your family.

44:05.845 --> 44:07.720
This is what you do to me?

44:07.804 --> 44:10.679
[both panting]

44:12.011 --> 44:13.261
Fuck you.

44:16.970 --> 44:19.053
And since you think
I owe you something,

44:19.136 --> 44:22.637
I won't tell my lawyer
you assaulted me.

44:22.720 --> 44:24.345
[knocking]

44:24.428 --> 44:26.053
[door opens]

44:26.136 --> 44:27.762
[door squeaking]

44:30.303 --> 44:32.303
[door closes]

44:32.387 --> 44:35.303
[train rattling]

44:35.387 --> 44:39.929
♪ hip-hop music ♪

44:40.011 --> 44:42.053
Excuse me, sir.
Would you like a candy bar?

44:43.762 --> 44:45.970
♪♪♪

44:46.053 --> 44:47.970
We've been out here
for three hours and only made

44:48.053 --> 44:49.637
eight dollars between us.

44:49.720 --> 44:52.428
Be patient.
Sales is the long game.

44:52.512 --> 44:54.720
[exhales]
I feel light headed.

44:54.804 --> 44:55.970
What you light headed for?

44:56.053 --> 44:57.053
Do not try to back out of this.

44:57.136 --> 44:58.637
I told you.

44:58.720 --> 45:00.428
I've been on
the Daniel Fast at church.

45:00.512 --> 45:02.261
But today is the last day.

45:02.345 --> 45:03.512
Praise Jesus.

45:03.595 --> 45:06.970
♪♪♪

45:07.053 --> 45:09.387
You've been on a Daniel Fast?

45:09.470 --> 45:13.345
And today's the last day?

45:13.428 --> 45:15.387
What?

45:15.470 --> 45:19.762
Bible says that obedience
is better than the sacrifice.

45:19.845 --> 45:21.845
Can I get some help
in here today?

45:21.929 --> 45:23.679
[cheers and applause]

45:23.762 --> 45:26.011
Aww, don't y'all go to looking
at your clocks.

45:26.095 --> 45:29.470
Because the Lord is speaking
and I'm still teaching.

45:29.553 --> 45:34.470
I said obedience
is better than a sacrifice.

45:34.553 --> 45:38.178
And through your obedience
all blessings will flow.

45:38.261 --> 45:39.845
Almost over.

45:39.929 --> 45:41.261
As soon as my daddy
get done preaching.

45:41.345 --> 45:42.637
He long winded.

45:42.720 --> 45:43.887
He been preaching
for a long time.

45:43.970 --> 45:45.136
How you know he almost done?

45:45.220 --> 45:46.178
Well...

45:46.261 --> 45:47.595
I say ten days.

45:47.679 --> 45:48.679
[congregation] Ten days.

45:48.762 --> 45:50.220
He just held up crackers.

45:50.303 --> 45:52.512
He always does that
at the end of a fast.

45:52.595 --> 45:54.387
[congregation shouting]

45:54.470 --> 45:56.804
Boy, I feel the anointing
of a four piece

45:56.887 --> 45:58.637
spicy dark in my spirit.

45:58.720 --> 46:01.261
Right now I receive it.

46:01.345 --> 46:02.720
[congregation] I receive it.

46:02.804 --> 46:05.053
I receive it.
You are dismissed.

46:05.136 --> 46:06.261
[cheers]

46:06.345 --> 46:08.178
[organ notes]

46:08.261 --> 46:09.470
- [Papa] Two dollars.
- [Kevin] Know you're hungry.

46:09.553 --> 46:11.053
[Papa] Get them before
they sell out.

46:11.136 --> 46:12.595
Selling over here.

46:12.679 --> 46:13.261
- Selling over here.
- Two dollars.

46:13.345 --> 46:14.387
Thank you, man.

46:14.470 --> 46:16.637
Two.
Two dollars.

46:16.720 --> 46:18.428
[Kevin] We got everything
over here.

46:18.512 --> 46:19.804
[Papa] Here we go, here we go.

46:19.887 --> 46:21.762
[Papa] Time is money, people.

46:21.845 --> 46:23.345
- I ain't trying to waste it.
- You make change here?

46:23.428 --> 46:25.512
[Kevin] Thank you, thank you,
thank you.

46:25.595 --> 46:26.887
We know you're hungry.

46:26.970 --> 46:28.637
Come on.
All right, here you go.

46:28.720 --> 46:30.512
- [woman] Give me four!
- There you go.

46:30.595 --> 46:31.804
♪ gospel vocalizing ♪

46:31.887 --> 46:33.387
We do good?

46:34.303 --> 46:37.637
[distant chatter]

46:45.261 --> 46:46.178
[cell phone rings]

46:46.261 --> 46:47.929
[phone trilling]

46:49.637 --> 46:50.929
[phone trilling]

46:51.011 --> 46:52.929
[phone ringing]

46:53.011 --> 46:53.720
[beeps]

46:53.804 --> 46:55.345
Hello?

46:55.428 --> 46:56.929
[woman] You are receiving
a call

46:57.011 --> 46:58.762
from a correctional
institution.

46:58.845 --> 47:00.553
Caller,
please state your name.

47:00.637 --> 47:03.512
♪ dramatic music ♪

47:03.595 --> 47:08.762
♪♪♪

47:09.345 --> 47:10.679
[Brandon] Hello?

47:10.762 --> 47:13.637
♪♪♪

47:13.720 --> 47:15.887
You can't put your hands
on my child like that, Ronnie.

47:15.970 --> 47:17.220
[Ronnie] I didn't mean
to hurt him.

47:17.303 --> 47:19.512
Let's not make a big deal
out of this.

47:19.595 --> 47:20.929
You know I love Jason.

47:21.011 --> 47:22.512
♪♪♪

47:22.595 --> 47:23.887
What's going on with you?

47:23.970 --> 47:25.720
You're not yourself.

47:25.804 --> 47:26.887
I don't want my son
to be scared of you.

47:26.970 --> 47:28.512
Hell, I don't wanna
be scared of you.

47:28.595 --> 47:30.178
I was just trying
to protect him, that's all.

47:30.261 --> 47:31.762
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Listen.

47:31.845 --> 47:33.136
I hear a lot of what you say,
Ronnie,

47:33.220 --> 47:35.261
but it's not lining up
with what you do.

47:35.345 --> 47:37.178
You love Jason.
You love me.

47:37.261 --> 47:38.970
You say you're applying
for all these city jobs.

47:39.053 --> 47:40.136
You say you're working
on finding us

47:40.220 --> 47:41.178
a better place to stay.

47:41.261 --> 47:42.303
But where is any of that?

47:42.387 --> 47:44.428
I'm waiting on people to call.

47:44.512 --> 47:46.053
Baby, I can't control all that.

47:46.136 --> 47:49.512
♪♪♪

47:49.595 --> 47:51.470
I need stability.

47:51.553 --> 47:54.387
I'm really trying, Trace.

47:54.470 --> 47:56.553
I swear to God, I am!

47:56.637 --> 47:58.470
Just...

47:58.553 --> 48:00.970
Just, if you can hang
in there with me.

48:01.053 --> 48:02.220
[grunts]

48:03.970 --> 48:06.428
I love you.
But I'm sorry.

48:06.512 --> 48:09.303
This is all just
too much for me right now.

48:10.929 --> 48:12.136
I think we need
to slow down a little.

48:12.220 --> 48:13.387
[scoffs]

48:13.470 --> 48:14.679
You know?

48:15.720 --> 48:16.929
Take a break.

48:22.679 --> 48:25.387
♪ dramatic music ♪

48:25.470 --> 48:30.345
♪♪♪

48:37.762 --> 48:38.929
[beeps]

48:39.011 --> 48:41.178
♪♪♪

48:41.261 --> 48:42.720
[beeps]

48:42.804 --> 48:46.929
♪♪♪

48:51.261 --> 48:52.345
Here.

48:52.428 --> 48:53.470
Here's all my tip money.

48:53.553 --> 48:54.553
You can have it.

48:54.637 --> 48:55.970
Go get his teeth checked.

48:58.679 --> 48:59.970
Thank you.

49:01.720 --> 49:03.637
You wanna come inside?

49:09.470 --> 49:10.762
Where EJ at?
He asleep?

49:10.845 --> 49:12.595
[door closes]

49:12.679 --> 49:14.470
I work early shifts on
Wednesdays so he's staying

49:14.553 --> 49:16.428
with my mama Tuesdays.

49:16.512 --> 49:18.095
I don't wanna mess up
his sleep schedule.

49:18.178 --> 49:19.637
Why the fuck you invite
me here, then?

49:19.720 --> 49:21.011
You knew I'd want to see him.

49:21.095 --> 49:22.512
You're always on some bullshit,
Tiff.

49:22.595 --> 49:25.053
I was trying to be nice
to your ass.

49:25.136 --> 49:26.178
I should go to your mom's
house right now

49:26.261 --> 49:27.512
so I can go see my son.

49:27.595 --> 49:28.553
[scoffs]
You don't wanna do that.

49:28.637 --> 49:29.595
My mama don't like you.

49:29.679 --> 49:31.095
She only don't like me

49:31.178 --> 49:32.345
'cause you're always
talking shit about me.

49:32.428 --> 49:33.804
No, she don't like you

49:33.887 --> 49:34.720
because you spent
the first year

49:34.804 --> 49:36.553
of EJ's life denying him.

49:36.637 --> 49:38.470
Now all of a sudden
he's your son.

49:38.553 --> 49:40.387
I've done everything
I'm supposed to do.

49:40.470 --> 49:42.387
You pay one month
of child support.

49:42.470 --> 49:44.136
That don't make you
daddy of the year.

49:44.220 --> 49:45.804
You ain't winning no
parenting awards, either.

49:45.887 --> 49:46.679
Fuck you, nigga.

49:46.762 --> 49:47.887
No, I used to fuck you.

49:47.970 --> 49:49.387
Now I don't.
That's why you mad.

49:49.470 --> 49:50.679
[train clacking]

49:50.762 --> 49:52.553
[grunts]

49:52.637 --> 49:55.637
♪ Queen Key's "Spenda Nite"
playing ♪

49:55.720 --> 49:58.261
♪ Queen, queen ♪

49:58.345 --> 50:00.553
♪ Queen shit bitch ♪

50:00.637 --> 50:02.261
♪ Queen ♪

50:02.345 --> 50:07.178
♪♪♪

50:09.512 --> 50:10.679
[both grunting]

50:10.762 --> 50:13.220
♪♪♪

50:13.303 --> 50:16.845
[both grunting]

50:16.929 --> 50:20.095
♪♪♪

50:20.178 --> 50:23.053
[indistinct radio chatter]

50:28.178 --> 50:31.053
♪ dramatic music ♪

50:31.136 --> 50:36.053
♪♪♪

50:41.679 --> 50:43.887
[door buzzes]

50:43.970 --> 50:48.428
♪♪♪

50:48.512 --> 50:49.470
[door closes]

50:49.553 --> 50:52.595
♪♪♪

50:52.679 --> 50:55.011
[gate buzzes]

50:55.095 --> 51:00.053
♪♪♪

51:00.136 --> 51:04.720
[distant sirens wailing]

51:04.804 --> 51:06.595
[gate squealing]

51:06.679 --> 51:08.595
[mechanics whirring]

51:08.679 --> 51:13.845
♪♪♪

51:21.011 --> 51:22.387
[whirring stops]

51:22.470 --> 51:27.387
♪♪♪

51:27.470 --> 51:29.929
[gate closing]

51:30.011 --> 51:35.095
♪♪♪

51:40.136 --> 51:43.553
If I keep up
my monthly payments,

51:43.637 --> 51:46.595
I was hoping the school
would make an exception

51:46.679 --> 51:49.345
and let me participate
in the After Taste.

51:49.428 --> 51:51.136
I'm just a young man
trying to do the right thing.

51:51.220 --> 51:53.261
What I'm saying is,

51:53.345 --> 51:55.887
I just need somebody
to believe in me.

51:55.970 --> 51:57.136
I get it.

51:58.887 --> 52:00.553
But this is a business,
Brandon.

52:00.637 --> 52:02.178
[indistinct chatter]

52:02.261 --> 52:05.053
If I let you slide,
I have to let others.

52:05.136 --> 52:07.261
I appreciate you taking
the time to see me.

52:07.345 --> 52:10.387
However our mission is not only
to train the next generation

52:10.470 --> 52:12.679
of great chefs but to encourage
people of strong character

52:12.762 --> 52:14.512
to pursue their dreams.

52:14.595 --> 52:18.011
I think we can count that
payment as a good faith effort

52:18.095 --> 52:21.720
and consider the name Brandon
Johnson to be in good standing.

52:21.804 --> 52:24.470
Thank you so much, Dean.
Thank you so much.

52:24.553 --> 52:27.804
Wait. There are no more
Brandon Johnsons, right?

52:27.887 --> 52:28.762
I don't think so.

52:28.845 --> 52:29.762
All right.

52:29.845 --> 52:30.845
But I'll check.

52:30.929 --> 52:31.595
All right, thank you.

52:34.762 --> 52:35.720
[Cruz] Jason's chain.

52:35.804 --> 52:37.220
[Ronnie] Yeah.

52:37.303 --> 52:38.261
[Cruz] So was he outside
the corner store?

52:38.345 --> 52:39.428
[Ronnie] Mm-hmm.

52:39.512 --> 52:40.679
[helicopter rotors whirring]

52:40.762 --> 52:41.595
[Ronnie] I took out the gun.

52:41.679 --> 52:43.679
[gunshot]

52:43.762 --> 52:45.595
[door opens]

52:45.679 --> 52:48.512
[indistinct chatter]

52:50.053 --> 52:52.970
[sirens blaring]

52:53.053 --> 52:55.845
[dog barking]

52:57.804 --> 52:59.637
[radio static]

52:59.720 --> 53:01.011
[Ronnie] Maximum range
of an M-16 A1 assault rifle

53:01.095 --> 53:02.845
is 3,600 meters.

53:02.929 --> 53:05.720
[Jason] Mom!
You're hurting me.

53:05.804 --> 53:07.804
[Tracy] You can't put your
hands on my child like that.

53:07.887 --> 53:09.345
I don't want my son
to be scared of you.

53:09.428 --> 53:11.220
Hell, I don't wanna
be scared of you.

53:11.303 --> 53:13.553
You love Jason.
You love me.

53:13.637 --> 53:16.095
You say you're applying
for all these city jobs.

53:16.178 --> 53:17.512
[Ethel] Your
disability's here.

53:17.595 --> 53:19.845
[Ronnie] Death
in milliseconds.

53:19.929 --> 53:21.553
[voices fade]

53:25.929 --> 53:28.804
♪ dramatic tones ♪

53:28.887 --> 53:30.553
[gunshot]

53:32.136 --> 53:34.679
[horn honking]

53:34.762 --> 53:36.303
Hey!

53:42.011 --> 53:44.720
♪ percussive music ♪

53:44.804 --> 53:49.929
♪♪♪

54:21.387 --> 54:24.261
♪ vocalizing ♪

54:24.345 --> 54:29.303
♪♪♪

55:13.762 --> 55:15.679
[keyboard clacking]

55:15.762 --> 55:16.762
[bell dings]

55:16.845 --> 55:17.845
♪♪♪
